>Description:
Zodiac's define-macro implementation gives unhelpful error messages when
the arity of the macro does not match the number of arguments applied to
it.
>How-To-Repeat:
Welcome to DrScheme, version 101/5d9.
Language: Graphical Full Scheme (MrEd).
> (define-macro m (lambda (x y) x))
> (m 1)
#<procedure>: expects 2 arguments, given 1: 1
> 
